text:
Jaeâ€™Lyn Withers 2024-25 Regular Season Highlights | North Carolina Forward
North Carolina forward Jae'Lyn Withers had an extremely productive second season for Hubert Davis and the Tar Heels during the 2024-25 campaign. Withers improved in nearly every aspect of his game and upped his scoring average from just over 4 points to 6.5 points per game for the year and his three-point shooting from 20% for the 2023-24 season to over 44% this year. The Charlotte, NC native pulled down 4.6 rebounds per game while shooting nearly 50% from the floor for the season.
